Real Madrid could be without left-back, Marcelo when they take on Paris Saint-Germain in their Champions League opener at Parc des Princes on Wednesday. Marcelo was diagnosed with a post-traumatic cervicodorsal injury on Monday. Real Madrid made this known in a statement on their official website on Monday. “After the tests carried out today on our player Marcelo by the Real Madrid Medical Services, he has been diagnosed with a post-traumatic cervicodorsal injury. “His recovery will continue to be assessed,” the statement read. Real Madrid head to the game following a 3-2 victory against Levante over the weekend. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.